    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:h 'rulerformat'` states that \n\n> The format of this option is like that of 'statusline'.\n\n\nHowever,  `:set rulerformat=%!toupper('foo')` returns `E539: Illegal character <!>: rulerformat=%!toupper('foo')`, while `:set statusline=%!toupper('foo')` works as expected.\n\nIt seems to me that either \n**(a)**: %! should work (my preferred solution), or\n**(b)** docs should be updated to reflect the difference. \n\nIf **(a)** is the way forward, I'm happy to try to patch.\n\nApologies if I'm missing something obvious here, I've tried to double-check everything but am new to the project üôè\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:set rulerformat=%!toupper('foo')\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nruler is set to `FOO`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.1.697\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.37.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nSystem Package Manager",
